==English==

===Interjection===
'''[[it's]] too [[late]] for [[sorry]]'''

# An [[expression]] of [[anger]] or [[disgust]] uttered toward someone who offers an [[apology]] after causing a situation to go very wrong, and a great deal of damage resulted.
#: ''The grieving mother who lost her daughter in an accident told the drunk driver "'''It's too late for sorry'''!" after he tried to apologize.''